If you are a crypto=C2=A0exchange, this is a nice opportunity. You have Cus=
tomer A who has Bitcoin and wants to borrow dollars, and Customer B who has=
 dollars and wants to borrow Bitcoin. (By =E2=80=9Cdollars,=E2=80=9D for a =
crypto exchange, I mostly mean =E2=80=9Cdollar-denominated stablecoins,=E2=
=80=9D though potentially also dollars.) You take some of Customer A=E2=80=
=99s Bitcoin and lend it to Customer B, and you take some of Customer B=E2=
=80=99s dollars and lend them to Customer A. Each of them is overcollateral=
ized =E2=80=94=C2=A0you only lend Customer A half the value of her Bitcoin,=
 and you only lend Customer B half the value of his dollars =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
so you feel pretty safe. And they both pay you interest.
But there are risks. One day Customer A might come in, pay off her dollar l=
oan, and ask to take her Bitcoin back. You don=E2=80=99t have her Bitcoin, =
or not all of them anyway; some of them are with Customer B. Customer B=C2=
=A0owes=C2=A0them to you =E2=80=94=C2=A0ultimately you=E2=80=99re good for =
it =E2=80=94=C2=A0but you don=E2=80=99t have them now. There is a timing pr=
oblem.
The solution to this is pretty much to have some extra cash =E2=80=94=C2=A0=
some of your own capital =E2=80=94=C2=A0to bridge these timing problems. Ev=
entually you=E2=80=99ll get the rest of the Bitcoin=C2=A0back from Customer=
 B, but for now you just pay Customer A out of your own Bitcoin stash.
But the timing problem is also connected to a real economic risk. If the pr=
ice of Bitcoin falls by 90%, Customer B will be thrilled. He will come to y=
ou and say =E2=80=9Chere=E2=80=99s my=C2=A0Bitcoin back, I=E2=80=99d like t=
o withdraw my dollars.=E2=80=9D But you don=E2=80=99t have his dollars, or =
not all of them; half of them are with Customer A. Your dollar loan to Cust=
omer A is now underwater: You loaned her 50% of the value of her Bitcoin, b=
ut Bitcoin fell by 90%, so she owes you more than her collateral is worth. =
You call her up and ask her for more money =E2=80=94=C2=A0a =E2=80=9Cmargin=
 call=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 but she, sensibly,=C2=A0doesn=E2=80=99t answer the=
